BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Being there without being there: Working with telepresence robots 
 (separate registration required\; conducted by Chemnitz University of Tech
 nology)
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260604T090000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260604T103000
DESCRIPTION:Spatially distributed work is now an integral part of working 
 life\, but it also brings new challenges. As part of Data Week\, we invite
  you to discover a new form of remote working: experience what it's like t
 o “be there without being there” with telepresence robots. Take part i
 n a short study or watch the application on video and share your experienc
 es with us. Together\, we will discuss the potential for different areas o
 f work.
LOCATION:Room 369
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Panel: Technically complicated and uncertain in terms of data prot
 ection law\, but unbeatably effective. Why civil society needs to have mor
 e confidence in AI. (Track: Between engagement and algorithms)
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260604T090000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/Berlin:20260604T103000
DESCRIPTION:Artificial intelligence (AI) is no longer a topic for the futu
 re\; it is already changing how we live\, work\, and engage with society. 
 But while companies and public authorities are increasingly using AI techn
 ologies\, civil society often lags behind. Is it too complex\, too uncerta
 in\, too many unanswered questions? Or is it a missed opportunity for grea
 ter public welfare\, participation\, and innovation?\nAI offers enormous p
 otential for civil society action\, from the automation of processes to da
 ta-based campaigns and new forms of participation. At the same time\, pres
 sing questions arise: How can data protection and ethics be guaranteed? Wh
 ere are the limits and risks? And how can AI be designed in such a way tha
 t it truly serves the common good?\nIn this discussion\, we want to highli
 ght specific examples\, challenges\, and solutions and discuss together ho
 w civil society can use AI responsibly and courageously.
LOCATION:Festsaal 
END:VEVENT
